The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 9: The government plans to set up eight more income tax overseas units, including in the US and the UK. I am hopeful these measures would result in seamless flow of tax related information from foreign jurisdictions and would strengthen our fight against the menace of tax evasion using cross border transactions, finance minister Pranab Mukherjee said.                             
	 Panaji, June 9: Tata Nano will be available without advance booking from August this year, Manoj Arora, senior manager of Tata Motors, said. From this August-September, customers will be able to walk into our showroom and drive out in a Nano, he said.                             
	 Singapore, June 9: Transport minister Kamal Nath today met top officials of Singapore investment firm Temasek with a proposal for setting up an infrastructure fund for India, which could have a corpus of about $2 billion.                            
	 New Delhi, June 9: The State Bank today hinted that the base rate that would replace the existing prime lending rate would be between 7.5 and 8.5 per cent.                             
	 Mumbai, June 9: The Life Insurance Corporation will share its database of over 21 crore policyholders with the Unique Identification Authority of India.
                                                                                                                          
